Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the fog radio access network (F-RAN) as a mobile networking architecture, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses radio resource allocation strategies to optimize spectral efficiency (SE) and energy efficiency (EE), which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the use of adaptive model selection schemes to improve SE and EE, which is related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the use of edge caching to improve SE and EE, which is related to multimedia. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not a major focus of the paper, the use of fog computing and edge caching may have security implications, which could fall under the scope of cryptography and security.
